                        <provenance type="found" when="1869">Found in 1869 by Brash (1879, 270) <q>lying on a low wall in the pleasure ground at the west side</q> of Salterbridge House (the residence of the Chearnley Family who were proprietors of the estate, which included the church and graveyard at Knockboy).
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed"> Redmond recorded and sketched the stone in 1885 (1885-6, 418-9) and a description with photograph appeared in Macalister's Studies in Irish Epigraphy in 1907 (213). The stone was reported lost by 1940 when Macalister (1945, 289) revisited Salterbridge. 
                        </provenance>
