            <div type="apparatus">
                 <listApp>
                    <app n="1">
                        <note><q>The prefixed MAQI is purely conjectural: nothing is left of it but the last two vowel-notches</q> (Macalister 1945, 289)</note>
                    </app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p></p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Neither of the personal names appear to be attested elsewhere but David Stifter has suggested Old Irish Mac-Mo-Guide* 'son-of-my-prayer' and Mo-Ibaite* 'my-drunken-one' (?).</p>
            </div>
